
    Thirty-seven people were believed killed in a fire that engulfed a shopping mall in the southern Philippine city of Davao, local authorities said on Sunday.A Bureau of Fire Protection commander at the scene said the chances of the 37 surviving were "zero", Paolo Duterte, Davao's vice mayor, who is also the president's son, wrote in a Facebook post.The blaze started at the four-storey NCCC Mall on Saturday morning and people were trapped inside, including at a call centre on the top floor, Ralph Canoy, a police officer in the district, told AFP.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstYlCKrjn6OcDo_OucKWlU80oOk2W9tnUnqWjzUSNjTZjCCnpRNqdDRdoLoAPSXCKvZD53QOAMZxfFQmZF9yz8elj40mFRu__wRMaHzz8iWuH8G0-m_M24Pu0riSM14C9rgGNXLIVG7aM8ihECsBMs_smJB5_EQpEBAzjy9nAr52u_2lQfuRbWI40AuWFAtDFV2TYpOebeUAhusxeKlp34jdxNdDVGhwtMG-gVndmgR3rt9ks9O8jSIT4M1BjtI8O83uQd0MsyMhTosv5ASC77uW0y1_9aiCaAG5Q\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzHeUNUTpf_rtEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
